 B. Smith Barbara Elaine Smith, known as B. Smith, is a restaurateur, model, author and television host; her show B. Smith With Style featured home decor and cooking segments and she is the author of three books focusing on recipes and food presentation. The lifestyle expert has been heralded as a “Renaissance woman” and a “domestic goddess”; she is a United States Culinary Ambassador and a Sirius XM radio celebrity. B. Smith launched a home collection with Bed Bath & Beyond in 2001 and a line of serveware in 2004. The serving ware product line consists of modern serveware with clean, classic lines and includes items such as chip & dip sets, three-tiered servers, multi-purpose servers with trays, appetizer bowls, wooden salad sets, stacking mugs, cheeseboards and pasta bowls. The home décor collection includes window curtain panels, quilts, table lamps, pillow shams, throw pillows, bed skirts, European pillow shams, casual bedding and more. 











